timeline.bodyText:
One annoying thing I found about this code is that this will not automatically update the values when visiting Etceteria until some varbit change happens after you're there. For instance, if you travel to Etceteria via spirit tree then leave right away, these conditions will never be met because isInKingdom() is false during the varbit changes while you're changing game states.
Because of the isKingdom() false negative, I propose this subscriber be changed somewhat to handle this case.

If inKingdom() is false and either coffer or favor values are 0, don't set any new values (this will be the case in some varbit changed events as the indexes are transmitted)
If inKingdom() is false, coffer and favor are both non-zero, and either of their values are different from the stored values, set lastChanged and the values (the server seems to send the last known values from visiting misc/etc--if we didn't get a varbitchanged on the island itself, we should update the values from varbit changes elsewhere in the world)
If inKingdom() is true and either value is different from the stored values, set lastChanged and the values

ie.
public void onVarbitChanged(VarbitChanged event)
{
	final int coffer = client.getVar(Varbits.KINGDOM_COFFER);
	final int favor = client.getVar(Varbits.KINGDOM_FAVOR);

	if (client.getGameState() == GameState.LOGGED_IN
		&& isThroneOfMiscellaniaCompleted()
		&& (isInKingdom() || coffer != 0 && favor != 0)
		&& (coffer != getCoffer() && favor != getFavor()))
	{
		setLastChanged(Instant.now());
		setCoffer(coffer);
		setFavor(favor);
	}

	processInfobox();
}

